            <thetext>Currently it is used like this:

qx.Class.isSubClassOf(myInstance.constructor, my.cool.SuperClass)

Note how the first argument requires &quot;.constructor&quot; while the second doesn&#39;t. This is some &quot;expert&quot; knowledge that the user of the API has to bring in.

Idea how to improve it:
Its usage would be more comfortable if isSubClassOf would be attached to every qooxdoo instance instead of being a static method of ax.Class. This would completely omit the need for the first parameter...</thetext>
